article.headline: Northern Iowa 74, Indiana State 64
article.story: CEDAR FALLS, Iowa (AP) -- Grant Stout scored 23 points and grabbed 12 rebounds and Travis Brown added 14 points to lead Northern Iowa past Indiana State 74-64 Saturday. Eric Coleman chipped in with 12 points and nine boards and Brooks McKowen had 12 points and six assists for Northern Iowa (15-4, 6-2 Missouri Valley), which moved into first place in the Valley with the win and Creighton's loss to Southern Illinois. The Panthers put the game away with a 23-7 run late in the second half. Brown started the spurt with back-to-back 3's, and Coleman and McKowen hit baskets to push Northern Iowa's lead to 58-48. McKowen followed with a 3-pointer to give the Panthers an 11-point lead with 2:32 left. Stout, who picked up his eighth double-double, was the only player to score a field goal for Northern Iowa during a 17-minute stretch between the end of the first half and midway through the second. Indiana State double-teamed Coleman most of the night, freeing up Stout to knock down a career-high five 3-pointers. Trent Wurtz led Indiana State (11-7, 4-4) with 21 points, and Gabe Moore and Marico Stinson each had 11.
